1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,440
<i>Previously on</i> Gotham...

2
00:00:01,520 --> 00:00:03,960
I had a meeting
with board of Wayne Enterprises.

3
00:00:04,040 --> 00:00:05,600
To tell them I was
investigating them,

4
00:00:05,680 --> 00:00:07,600
they sent someone
we trust to spy on us.

5
00:00:07,680 --> 00:00:10,760
Alfred was stabbed.
It was a friend of his from the Army.

6
00:00:10,840 --> 00:00:13,000
- What was he looking for?
- Some of my files missing.

7
00:00:13,080 --> 00:00:16,040
I could find out who hired him.
He's the key to everything.

8
00:00:16,120 --> 00:00:17,160
I have a plan.

9
00:00:17,240 --> 00:00:18,360
I promise you,

10
00:00:18,440 --> 00:00:20,600
I will get some of us
out of here alive.

11
00:00:20,680 --> 00:00:23,680
- Who are you?
- Dr. Francis Dulmacher.

12
00:00:23,760 --> 00:00:26,120
The people in the basement trust me.

13
00:00:26,200 --> 00:00:30,800
Put me in charge and I promise you
a dependable flow of healthy product.

14
00:00:30,880 --> 00:00:33,000
- And if I fail?
- Those who fail me

15
00:00:33,080 --> 00:00:35,040
still have their uses.

16
00:00:35,120 --> 00:00:36,120
What are they doing?

17
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:38,320
I'm sorry, honey, you're on the list.

18
00:00:38,400 --> 00:00:40,800
Half the cops on the G.C.P.D.
have a Cobblepot

19
00:00:40,880 --> 00:00:43,360
and Loeb has the goods on
all of them.

20
00:00:43,440 --> 00:00:44,720
That is what Loeb does.

21
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:47,000
- Well, it ends now.
- So, what do you want?

22
00:00:47,080 --> 00:00:48,080
With the coming election

23
00:00:48,160 --> 00:00:50,920
for president
of the policeman's union

24
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:53,040
there's no man I'd rather support.

25
00:00:53,120 --> 00:00:55,360
It's a new day in the G.C.P.D.

26
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:24,680
- Looking good, Ms. Cavanaugh.
- Thank you.

27
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:26,440
- How's that swelling?
- Fine.

28
00:01:26,520 --> 00:01:29,840
If you need more ice packs,
I'll let Denise know.

29
00:01:29,920 --> 00:01:32,160
Mr. Douglas,
I know you don't like your view

30
00:01:32,240 --> 00:01:34,080
and as soon as
a recovery suite is open

31
00:01:34,160 --> 00:01:35,720
I'm going to move you.

32
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:17,080
Is there a problem?

33
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:19,720
- You're outside.
- You're observant.

34
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:22,120
I'm the new assistant for the doctor.
I'm Fish.

35
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:23,480
And you are?

36
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:27,040
Inside, you're free to roam,
that's Dr. Dulmacher's prerogative.

37
00:02:27,120 --> 00:02:30,560
But once you step outside,
you're in my world.

38
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:33,600
I'm the man who catches
the poor souls

39
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:35,760
brave enough to try to escape.

40
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:37,320
You're the catcher.

41
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:38,840
I've heard a lot about you.

42
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:42,840
So, have there been many?

43
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:44,400
Poor souls, I mean.

44
00:02:44,480 --> 00:02:45,480
No.

45
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:48,200
The water does most of the work.

46
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:54,280
But every so often, someone gets
stupid and gives it a go.

47
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:56,760
I didn't know
I wasn't supposed to be outside.

48
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:57,880
My mistake.

49
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:01,360
Make that mistake again

50
00:03:01,440 --> 00:03:02,720
and it'll be your last.

51
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:16,440
I saw the papers the other day.

52
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:18,840
- Congratulations.
- Thanks.

53
00:03:18,920 --> 00:03:22,680
So, what does president
of the policeman's union do exactly?

54
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:24,960
Depends on the president.

55
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:26,600
- I see.
- How's Alfred?

56
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:30,080
Whinier than I thought.

57
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:32,040
No, he's getting better.

58
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:34,480
Glad to hear it.

59
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:41,000
You two lied about who stabbed him,
didn't you?

60
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,480
That's why you're here?

61
00:03:45,360 --> 00:03:46,560
Is it?

62
00:03:46,640 --> 00:03:47,640
Yes.

63
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:51,080
Did you...

64
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:53,880
lie to me?

65
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:56,520
No.

66
00:03:57,640 --> 00:03:59,200
If we don't have a description
of the culprit

67
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:00,400
we won't find him.

68
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:04,280
I wish I could help you, detective.

69
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:09,280
Alfred wants to go after him

70
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:11,720
on his own,
that's why you lied to me.

71
00:04:13,040 --> 00:04:14,320
No.

72
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:16,680
Bruce, look at me.

73
00:04:16,760 --> 00:04:20,120
Whatever Alfred is up to,
you have to stay out of it.

74
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:21,680
It's dangerous.

75
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:23,680
And it's not your fight.

76
00:04:23,760 --> 00:04:25,600
I cut this bread way too thick,
didn't I?

77
00:04:25,680 --> 00:04:26,680
Bruce...

78
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:30,920
I understand what you're saying.

79
00:04:36,280 --> 00:04:37,280
Okay, then.

80
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:51,520
Detective Gordon.

81
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:54,400
Len Moore.

82
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:57,360
- Officer. What can I help you with?
- You're a man with a reputation.

83
00:04:57,440 --> 00:04:58,920
- Yeah?
- A Gotham detective

84
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:01,200
who actually closes cases.

85
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:02,640
I try.

86
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:09,120
That's actually why I'm here.

87
00:05:09,200 --> 00:05:10,600
- Yeah?
- See a few weeks ago

88
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:12,160
I was the first responder
to a homicide.

89
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:13,720
Victim's name was 'Grace Fairchild'.

90
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:16,800
They found her body stabbed
to death.

91
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,560
The detectives who caught the case

92
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:20,520
they got nowhere with it
and moved on.

93
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:21,840
I'm sorry to hear that

94
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:23,720
- but it happens.
- I'm wondering if you'd pick up

95
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,080
where they left off.

96
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:27,920
You want me to take over the case?

97
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,400
Yeah.

98
00:05:29,480 --> 00:05:31,880
Look, Len, I got a full boat here.

99
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:35,200
This victim's family,
they deserve justice.

100
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:37,480
- Yeah.
- Her killer deserves to pay

101
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:39,240
for what he did.

102
00:05:39,320 --> 00:05:40,480
This was a nasty one.

103
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:43,920
They're all nasty.
What's your angle on this?

104
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:46,400
There's no angle. It's just...

105
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:49,240
A few of us younger guys,

106
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:51,240
and we've been watching
what you've been doing

107
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:55,160
to clean up Gotham and the G.C.P.D.,
and I wanna be a part of it.

108
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:57,360
And bringing you this case...

109
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:59,280
is my way of trying to do that.

110
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:05,720
I'll look into it.

111
00:06:15,400 --> 00:06:16,440
Ready to go?

112
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:18,760
Ready?

113
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:20,600
I have been dreaming
about the carbonara

114
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:22,200
at Luccio's all day.

115
00:06:22,280 --> 00:06:24,080
New case?

116
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:27,520
Sort of. It's an unsolved homicide
a uni asked me to look into.

117
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:30,880
- It's an odd one.
- How so?

118
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:32,000
Thought you were hungry.

119
00:06:33,080 --> 00:06:34,280
What can I say?

120
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:35,720
You had me at "homicide."

121
00:06:36,640 --> 00:06:39,680
The victim, Grace Fairchild,
was found two weeks ago.

122
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:42,920
But she was reported missing
four months earlier.

123
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:45,280
The last anyone heard,
she called her mother

124
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:48,440
said she was having a drink at a bar
in the South Village.

125
00:06:48,520 --> 00:06:50,800
That's my neighborhood. What bar?

126
00:06:50,880 --> 00:06:53,280
Detectives canvassed the area,
nobody knows.

127
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:54,480
No leads, no tips.

128
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:57,240
I'm starting to see
why the case was dropped.

129
00:06:57,320 --> 00:06:58,680
God, we were almost the same age.

130
00:06:58,760 --> 00:07:00,200
We could've been friends.

131
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:04,800
You know, they have a few
speakeasies in the South Village.

132
00:07:04,880 --> 00:07:05,880
It's a new thing.

133
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:08,640
You walk in through a dry cleaner's
or a shoe store to get inside.

134
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:10,720
Easy to miss
if you're not in the know.

135
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,800
Thanks. I'll check it out.

136
00:07:12,880 --> 00:07:14,000
Good.

137
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:16,480
I'm glad you're looking into this.

138
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:18,760
Whoever did this, he's a monster.

139
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:32,760
Kelly.

140
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:37,520
God.

141
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:40,240
Still bad.

142
00:07:41,320 --> 00:07:42,760
What do you want?

143
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:46,600
I have a plan, but I need your help.

144
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:47,880
What plan?

145
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:53,160
We're going to escape.

146
00:07:54,400 --> 00:07:57,160
I'm getting off of this hell
of an island

147
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:58,880
or I'm gonna die trying.

148
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:21,760
{\an5}Alfred?

149
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:26,920
{\an5}Where are you going?

150
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:29,000
{\an5}Into the city, Master Bruce.

151
00:08:29,080 --> 00:08:30,800
{\an5}If I know Reggie,
he's probably drunk himself

152
00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:33,200
{\an5}half to death by now

153
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:36,320
{\an5}and is moving swiftly
onto the harder stuff.

154
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:38,040
{\an5}I'll probably find him

155
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:40,720
{\an5}holed up in a shooting gallery,
totally off his maracas.

156
00:08:41,720 --> 00:08:43,680
{\an5}Alfred, you can't go.

157
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:46,520
- You're not well.
- No choice, Master Bruce.

158
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:49,080
{\an5}He'll only be here for a few days.

159
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:51,280
{\an5}Enough time to get his fix,
then he'll be off.

160
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:55,520
{\an5}Well, then we'd better get going.

161
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:57,920
If you think I'm gonna take you,
Master...

162
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:08,840
Oh, dear.

163
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:19,680
{\an5}Good day, Lidia.

164
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:20,800
{\an5}Have you thought about my offer?

165
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:24,280
{\an5}I told you already,
my place is not for sale.

166
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:25,960
{\an5}Please.

167
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:28,480
{\an5}I beg of you, think again.

168
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:31,560
{\an5}I will serve strictly
as a silent partner.

169
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:35,600
{\an5}You will continue
to run the day-to-day operations...

170
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:37,000
I told you already!

171
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:39,880
Madam, please, I meant no harm.

172
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:42,000
Okay, ma'am. You made your point.

173
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:44,080
Madam, I assure you...

174
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:47,840
{\an5}I have a sincere interest
in your establishment.

175
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:50,680
{\an5}If money is not what you seek...

176
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:52,840
{\an5}surely there is something you want.

177
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:58,840
{\an5}My granddaughter, Antonia...

178
00:09:58,920 --> 00:10:00,160
{\an5}She's beautiful...

179
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,520
{\an5}Virtuous...

180
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:03,960
{\an5}An angel.

181
00:10:05,680 --> 00:10:12,040
{\an5}And she has been seduced
by a silver-tongued guitar player.

182
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:13,480
Lucifer himself.

183
00:10:13,560 --> 00:10:15,480
A tragedy.

184
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:17,720
{\an5}You make her come home...

185
00:10:18,880 --> 00:10:21,800
{\an5}leave this baboon...

186
00:10:24,520 --> 00:10:27,640
then I'll consider your offer.

187
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:28,720
Madam...

188
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:31,720
She'll be home for Sunday Mass.

189
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:34,440
You have my word.

190
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:42,760
This place is a dump.
Real nickel-and-dime.

191
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:44,800
It's worth far more than that, Gabe.

192
00:10:44,880 --> 00:10:46,320
You just don't see it yet.

193
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,400
- No.
- I'm not saying

194
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:51,280
we officially take over
the investigation.

195
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:52,360
Just help me look into it.

196
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:53,760
No.

197
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:56,120
Harvey, the victim deserves justice.

198
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:58,320
Yeah,
and I deserve a mute supermodel

199
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:00,840
who likes pasty Irish guys
and loves to cook.

200
00:11:00,920 --> 00:11:05,040
It's not happening.
Besides, we both know that justice

201
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:07,160
isn't the real reason
you want this one.

202
00:11:07,240 --> 00:11:08,440
Hello, detectives.

203
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:10,480
Ed, question.

204
00:11:10,560 --> 00:11:13,800
Would you rather work more or less?

205
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:15,440
- Is this a riddle?
- Exactly.

206
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:17,800
You're helping. What's up?

207
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:20,000
List of establishments
in the South Village

208
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:21,120
with a liquor license.

209
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:23,200
- Including speakeasies?
- Yes, sirree.

210
00:11:23,280 --> 00:11:25,280
Four of which,
you'll be pleased to know,

211
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:26,960
were missed
by the original detectives.

212
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:29,720
That's great, Ed.
Thanks. One more thing.

213
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:31,240
I was going through
the crime scene evidence

214
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:32,880
from the Fairchild murder and...

215
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:35,320
there's a piece of evidence missing.

216
00:11:36,480 --> 00:11:38,920
- Any idea what it is?
- No, but it's labeled "3A."

217
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,000
Think you can find it?

218
00:11:40,080 --> 00:11:42,360
Detective, I will solve this puzzle.

219
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:51,120
You coming?

220
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:54,120
Let me say it in Spanish. No.

221
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:56,520
Okay, look, you're right.
I'm ambitious.

222
00:11:56,600 --> 00:12:00,800
I wanna show people around here
that things are gonna change.

223
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:02,920
But, Harvey,
I can't do that without your help.

224
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:04,320
Look, I know you're riding high

225
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:06,600
with getting over on
Loeb and all

226
00:12:06,680 --> 00:12:09,480
but there's one thing
you should always remember.

227
00:12:09,560 --> 00:12:13,680
Fly too close to the sun,
you're gonna get burned.

228
00:12:13,760 --> 00:12:15,360
- You done?
- Yeah.

229
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:16,920
Good. Then get your ass up.

230
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:23,080
<i>So that's it.</i>

231
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:26,120
So you're trying to tell me

232
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:28,120
you actually think
we can get out of here?

233
00:12:29,280 --> 00:12:31,200
That's what I said, didn't I?

234
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:35,360
- How?
- With cunning and guile.

235
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:37,240
But it won't work without your help.

236
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:40,240
Why us?

237
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:41,920
Why not your friends?

238
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:44,840
There's no telling
how this is all going to go down

239
00:12:44,920 --> 00:12:46,240
during the breakout.

240
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:48,480
Just in case it goes south.

241
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:50,120
I need some stone-cold killers

242
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:53,560
by my side
not some whipped-ass victims.

243
00:12:53,640 --> 00:12:55,960
That's fair. What's the plan?

244
00:12:56,040 --> 00:12:58,640
Outside, there's a boat
down by the shore

245
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:01,720
big enough to carry the six of us
off of this island.

246
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:02,800
A boat?

247
00:13:04,440 --> 00:13:05,880
You have a better idea?

248
00:13:05,960 --> 00:13:08,120
I heard a chopper land the other day.

249
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:09,600
Thumped like a son of a bitch.

250
00:13:09,680 --> 00:13:11,760
Why don't we fly out of here?

251
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:14,760
Do any of you know how to fly
a helicopter?

252
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:20,760
That's why.

253
00:13:20,840 --> 00:13:23,560
All right, this boat.

254
00:13:23,640 --> 00:13:25,640
You got the keys to it?

255
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:28,120
No. Not yet, but I will.

256
00:13:29,880 --> 00:13:32,680
So, are you in or out?

257
00:13:35,640 --> 00:13:37,120
We're 0-3 and
my dogs are barking.

258
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:39,560
I'm hardly one to complain
about going to a bar,

259
00:13:39,640 --> 00:13:41,200
but this is getting ridiculous.

