00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:11,360
- Unless what?
- Have you ever consider

346
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:12,600
if she ran off on her own?

347
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:15,440
That her going missing has
nothing to do with her murder?

348
00:19:15,520 --> 00:19:17,520
The findings would certainly
support that.

349
00:19:19,520 --> 00:19:20,520
Maybe.

350
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:26,040
No.

351
00:19:26,920 --> 00:19:30,040
No. Fairchild had a good job,
a mortgage.

352
00:19:30,120 --> 00:19:33,000
Hell, she called her mother
the night she went missing.

353
00:19:33,080 --> 00:19:35,600
No, she didn't run away.
She was taken.

354
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:39,160
And whoever took her
kept her locked away

355
00:19:40,520 --> 00:19:42,000
