Wait. Stop. Wait, wait.

394
00:23:30,640 --> 00:23:33,600
I was lying,
but I wasn't trying to escape.

395
00:23:33,680 --> 00:23:35,520
You were going to kill me?

396
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:37,080
Slit my throat, perhaps?

397
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:40,040
No, I swear.

398
00:23:41,240 --> 00:23:42,240
Not yours.

399
00:23:43,320 --> 00:23:44,320
Not yours.

400
00:23:48,280 --> 00:23:52,400
Every night when I close my eyes,
I pray to God...

401
00:23:52,480 --> 00:23:55,240
that nightmare doesn't come.

402
00:23:56,240 --> 00:23:57,240
That...

403
00:23:58,440 --> 00:24:01,960
living, breathing man
stitched together with...

404
00:24:03,680 --> 00:24:06,120
arms and legs that weren't his.

405
00:24:06,200 --> 00:24:07,680
That nightmare you created...

406
00:24:08,920 --> 00:24:11,080
I've faced dangerous men

407
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:14,240
but none like you.

408
00:24:16,640 --> 00:24:18,240
Dollmaker.

409
00:24:19,320 --> 00:24:22,960
So, you'd rather take your own life
than end up one of my creations?

410
00:24:23,040 --> 00:24:24,040
Yes.

411
00:24:27,680 --> 00:24:29,120
Well,

412
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:30,720
Miss Mooney.

413
00:24:30,800 --> 00:24:34,120
Try anything like this again
and your nightmare will come true.

414
00:24:35,280 --> 00:24:37,960
I will bring you back
from the dead if I have to.

415
00:24:39,440 --> 00:24:42,960
And make you into something
the world has never seen.

416
00:24:49,400 --> 00:24:50,880
Was there something else?

417
00:24:54,320 --> 00:24:55,320
No.

418
00:25:16,720 --> 00:25:19,280
I could've smashed your head
with a brick, you know.

419
00:25:19,360 --> 00:25:21,040
Why would you do that?

420
00:25:21,120 --> 00:25:22,240
Why'd you even say that?

421
00:25:22,320 --> 00:25:23,720
Just thought you should know.

422
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:25,480
What's up?
Why are you looking for me?

423
00:25:26,640 --> 00:25:27,920
Reggie Payne,

424
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:30,240
the man who stabbed Alfred,
he's in Gotham.

425
00:25:30,320 --> 00:25:32,200
And you need my help to find him.
Okay.

426
00:25:34,040 --> 00:25:36,600
Alfred said he'd be at a gun range
for a few days.

427
00:25:36,680 --> 00:25:39,120
But I checked every one in the city.
Nothing.

428
00:25:39,200 --> 00:25:41,160
Who stays at a gun range
for a few days?

429
00:25:42,840 --> 00:25:44,000
Doesn't make any sense.

430
00:25:44,080 --> 00:25:45,920
That's what he said.

