sometimes for months.

529
00:33:54,280 --> 00:33:56,840
Then he dumps
their bodies around Gotham.

530
00:33:56,920 --> 00:33:59,520
- How many has he killed?
- A dozen. Maybe more.

531
00:33:59,600 --> 00:34:01,920
Every time he makes a kill,
he leaves one of these

532
00:34:02,000 --> 00:34:05,000
at the crime scene.
It's his calling card.

533
00:34:05,080 --> 00:34:06,360
So, who is he?

534
00:34:06,440 --> 00:34:08,480
No one knows.

535
00:34:08,560 --> 00:34:11,560
Thinking is he's educated,
decent-looking, rich,

536
00:34:11,640 --> 00:34:12,680
but that's just a profile.

537
00:34:12,760 --> 00:34:15,600
Some of the guys call him
the Don Juan Killer.

538
00:34:15,680 --> 00:34:16,720
Most call him the Ogre.

539
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:20,120
So, why haven't I heard
about this guy before?

540
00:34:20,200 --> 00:34:21,600
Why hasn't the public?

541
00:34:21,680 --> 00:34:23,360
- It's the G.C.P.D.'s...
- Hey, fellas.

542
00:34:25,320 --> 00:34:27,120
Dirty little secret.

543
00:34:27,200 --> 00:34:29,760
Only a handful of senior detectives
know anything about this guy.

544
00:34:29,840 --> 00:34:31,560
And they sure ain't leaking it
to the press.

545
00:34:31,640 --> 00:34:32,760
Why not?

546
00:34:32,840 --> 00:34:37,200
Because the Ogre retaliates
against any cop who investigates him.

547
00:34:37,280 --> 00:34:40,080
He kills the people they love.

548
00:34:40,160 --> 00:34:42,480
That's why this lunatic
hasn't been caught yet, Jim

549
00:34:42,560 --> 00:34:44,960
because no one's been stupid enough
to investigate.

550
00:34:47,960 --> 00:34:49,160
Until I came along.

551
00:34:49,240 --> 00:34:51,760
Which makes me wonder,
how did you catch this?

552
00:34:51,840 --> 00:34:54,440
I told you, a fellow officer asked me
to look into it.

553
00:34:54,520 --> 00:34:56,080
Who?

554
00:34:56,160 --> 00:34:57,160
Which one?

555
00:35:19,240 --> 00:35:20,840
Okay.

556
00:35:20,920 --> 00:35:22,800
- <i>Other side.</i>
- That's him.

557
00:35:25,680 --> 00:35:27,120
<i>Give me some of that stuff.</i>

558
00:35:44,640 --> 00:35:47,360
Relax, old man.
We're not gonna rob you.

559
00:35:47,440 --> 00:35:50,200
- What are you doing here?
- We came to talk to you.

560
00:35:50,280 --> 00:35:52,560
- Who's she?
- Never mind.

561
00:35:52,640 --> 00:35:54,560
Who sent you to my house?

562
00:35:54,640 --> 00:35:56,000
Who sent me to...

563
00:35:57,480 --> 00:35:59,480
Just go home. Go home, Bruce.

564
00:35:59,560 --> 00:36:01,720
You'll be in more trouble
than you are already.

565
00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:05,160
Hey! That's my medicine.
Give me that.

566
00:36:05,240 --> 00:36:07,160
My friend just asked you a question.

567
00:36:07,240 --> 00:36:08,560
I said, give me that.

568
00:36:08,640 --> 00:36:09,680
Or you'll what?

569
00:36:14,640 --> 00:36:17,360
- Hey! Don't!
- Answer the question.

570
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:25,200
Listen, I didn't mean any harm.

571
00:36:25,280 --> 00:36:27,960
I just was to take some documents.

572
00:36:28,040 --> 00:36:29,520
But Alfred walked in...

573
00:36:31,920 --> 00:36:33,240
is he all right?

574
00:36:35,040 --> 00:36:36,760
Is he?

575
00:36:36,840 --> 00:36:38,040
You stabbed him.

576
00:36:39,960 --> 00:36:41,240
What do you care?

577
00:36:41,320 --> 00:36:43,800
I care. He's all right, isn't he?

578
00:36:45,920 --> 00:36:47,320
Who sent you?

579
00:36:50,160 --> 00:36:51,960
Throw them out.

580
00:36:52,040 --> 00:36:54,280
- No!
- Tell me who sent you.

581
00:36:56,280 --> 00:36:57,480
Who sent you?

582
00:36:59,320 --> 00:37:01,040
You shouldn't be doing this, Bruce.

583
00:37:02,240 --> 00:37:05,240
Only Alfie can deal
with these people.

584
00:37:05,320 --> 00:37:06,760
What people?

585
00:37:10,560 --> 00:37:12,920
It's a woman named Mathis,

586
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:14,400
and a guy called Bunderslaw.

587
00:37:14,480 --> 00:37:18,360
Sid Bunderslaw.
He's the guy I dealt with.

588
00:37:18,440 --> 00:37:19,520
But you've go...

589
00:37:19,600 --> 00:37:22,040
You've got to let
Alfie take care of this.

590
00:37:22,120 --> 00:37:25,040
Not you, Bruce.
It's no business for a child.

591
00:37:25,120 --> 00:37:26,560
This man, Bunderslaw.

592
00:37:28,000 --> 00:37:29,840
What did he want?

593
00:37:29,920 --> 00:37:32,200
Just to know what you knew.

594
00:37:32,280 --> 00:37:35,680
To see how far your investigation
had gone.

595
00:37:35,760 --> 00:37:37,360
But he was scared.

596
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:41,440
And that's why he sent me.

597
00:37:41,520 --> 00:37:44,320
Now, can I have my bag back, please?

598
00:37:44,400 --> 00:37:45,760
Please?

599
00:37:48,840 --> 00:37:50,240
Give it back to him.

600
00:38:05,800 --> 00:38:06,920
You.

601
00:38:07,880 --> 00:38:09,920
You're a sick man, Mr. Payne.

602
00:38:11,400 --> 00:38:12,920
You need help.

603
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:14,880
Don't you patronize me.

604
00:38:16,640 --> 00:38:20,680
I may have vices, yeah,
but I'm a professional.

605
00:38:22,960 --> 00:38:26,760
You want me to tell Bunderslaw
that you're onto him?

606
00:38:26,840 --> 00:38:29,400
Because he'll come after you.

607
00:38:29,480 --> 00:38:33,560
And there's nothing that you can do
to stop him.

608
00:38:34,920 --> 00:38:38,160
You're just silly little children.

609
00:38:40,320 --> 00:38:42,440
I'm going to tell on you.

610
00:39:01,480 --> 00:39:02,880
No, you won't.

611
00:39:31,800 --> 00:39:34,640
It wa... it wasn't my idea. I swear.

612
00:39:34,720 --> 00:39:36,480
I was ordered to get you
to take the case.

613
00:39:36,560 --> 00:39:38,360
- Ordered by who?
- Loeb.

614
00:39:40,240 --> 00:39:41,520
It was Commissioner Loeb.

615
00:39:46,520 --> 00:39:48,400
He told me to tell you that...

616
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:52,960
I looked up to you,
that you inspired me.

617
00:39:53,040 --> 00:39:56,960
I mean, he told me to say that
I wanted to help clean up Gotham

618
00:39:57,040 --> 00:39:58,920
and the G.C.P.D,

619
00:39:59,000 --> 00:40:00,160
and that this case...

620
00:40:01,600 --> 00:40:02,840
this case was part of that.

621
00:40:05,040 --> 00:40:06,080
He knew you couldn't say no.

622
00:40:08,120 --> 00:40:10,680
So you followed orders
like a good soldier.

623
00:40:10,760 --> 00:40:12,240
I didn't have a choice.

624
00:40:13,880 --> 00:40:16,560
I mean, you know what Loeb can do.

625
00:40:20,720 --> 00:40:21,920
All too well.

626
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:26,640
Jim, listen,
you're still in the clear on this.

627
00:40:26,720 --> 00:40:27,960
In the clear?
He could come after Lee.

628
00:40:28,040 --> 00:40:30,520
Only if he thinks
you're investigating him.

629
00:40:30,600 --> 00:40:32,160
Think about it.

630
00:40:32,240 --> 00:40:33,600
It's not on your docket.

631
00:40:33,680 --> 00:40:35,280
There's been no press
linking you to this case.

632
00:40:35,360 --> 00:40:38,240
All we've done is ask questions,
so you gotta drop it now.

633
00:40:38,320 --> 00:40:40,080
This is no time to be a hero.

634
00:40:40,160 --> 00:40:42,800
If I drop it,
I'm letting a serial killer go free.

635
00:40:42,880 --> 00:40:44,720
The blood of his next victim
is on my hands.

636
00:40:44,800 --> 00:40:46,520
If you don't drop it,
that blood could be Lee's.

637
00:40:50,400 --> 00:40:53,840
<i>Hi, you've reached Lee.
Go ahead and leave a message.</i>

638
00:40:53,920 --> 00:40:56,400
Lee, call me as soon as you can.
It's very important.

639
00:41:03,480 --> 00:41:05,360
You!

640
00:41:05,440 --> 00:41:07,200
- You son of a bitch.
- Excuse me?

641
00:41:07,280 --> 00:41:08,320
You set me up.

642
00:41:08,400 --> 00:41:10,680
- Detective, I don't know what...
- Don't talk.

643
00:41:10,760 --> 00:41:12,600
- Listen. Back off.
- Hey.

644
00:41:12,680 --> 00:41:13,680
Don't you...

645
00:41:16,280 --> 00:41:17,360
I tried to work with you.

646
00:41:18,640 --> 00:41:20,640
But now you crossed a line.

647
00:41:20,720 --> 00:41:22,600
You come after the one I love?

648
00:41:24,680 --> 00:41:27,480
From here on, we're playing my way.

649
00:41:27,560 --> 00:41:30,360
No more games. No more deals.

650
00:41:30,440 --> 00:41:33,200
I'm gonna find the Ogre,
and I'm gonna put him behind bars.

651
00:41:33,280 --> 00:41:35,240
And when I've done that,
I'm coming after you.

652
00:41:36,520 --> 00:41:39,280
I'm coming after you, commissioner.

653
00:41:39,360 --> 00:41:40,560
You're done.

